{"id":4157,"date":"2024-12-16T14:18:14","date_gmt":"2024-12-16T14:18:14","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=4157"},"modified":"2024-12-16T16:39:36","modified_gmt":"2024-12-16T16:39:36","slug":"fossil-reviver","status":"publish","type":"wiki","link":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/misc-info\/useful-npcs\/fossil-reviver\/","title":{"rendered":"Fossil Reviver (NPC)"},"content":{"rendered":"<table class=\"table grey left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Location<\/th>\n<td><strong>Gurun Town<\/strong> &#8211; Inside the house east of the Gurun Town KBT Expressway entrance<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Purpose<\/th>\n<td>Revives any fossil the player may have in their inventory<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Transaction Item<\/th>\n<td>N\/A<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cost<\/th>\n<td>N\/A<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Location<\/h2>\n<p>Fly to the Gurun Town Pokemon Center and follow the brown path north. Enter the house directly north of the Pokemon Center and east of the KBT Expressway entrance.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/01-pokemon-unbound-entering-the-fossil-revivers-house.jpg\" alt=\"Entering the Fossil Reviver\u2019s house. \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Entering the Fossil Reviver\u2019s house.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The Fossil Reviver is the only NPC inside of the house.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/02-pokemon-unbound-approaching-the-fossil-reviver.jpg\" alt=\"Approaching the Fossil Reviver. \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Approaching the Fossil Reviver.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h2>Purpose<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/03-pokemon-unbound-giving-the-fossil-reviver-a-fossil.jpg\" alt=\"Giving the Fossil Reviver a fossil. \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Giving the Fossil Reviver a fossil.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The Fossil Reviver can revive any fossil in your inventory for free. <\/p>\n<p>Simply give her a fossil, then exit and re-enter her house to finish the reviving process. Then speak with her again to get the revived Pok\u00e9mon.<\/p>\n<div class=\"callout-box\"><strong>Tip:<\/strong> If you&#8217;re looking for fossils then you can get them <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/items\/rock-smash-items\/\">as Rock Smash items by smashing breakable rocks<\/a>.<\/div>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/misc-info\/useful-npcs\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"299\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/11\/useful-npc-preview.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/11\/useful-npc-preview.jpg 300w, https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/11\/useful-npc-preview-200x200.jpg 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">Useful NPCs<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":4158,"parent":2143,"menu_order":2,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[],"class_list":["post-4157","wiki","type-wiki","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/4157","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/wiki"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unb